cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the analysis of Android apps and proposes a novel system for recovering contextual information around limited-quantity audit logs. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with identifying and mitigating threats to Android users. Additionally, the paper also mentions improving the performance of existing analysis tools, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of control-flow graphs, which is a common technique in programming languages (cs.PL). The proposed algorithm for log matching involves finding a path, which can be related to system control and automation (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques to recover contextual information, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
